  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposal due to the loss of the original chimney stack feature of the host building and erection of an unsympathetic mansard  roof extension which would  be visible from the street and surrounds would be harmful to the architectural character of the host building and would  disrupt the largely unaltered roofline of the terrace in which it is situated, to the detriment of the appearance of the surrounding area.  The proposal therefore fails to accord with policies 2.4.1, 2.4.2  and 2.4.3 of the statutory Urban Design Guide (2006) SPD,  the National Planning Policy Framework (2011); policies CS8 & CS9 (Protecting and Enhancing Islington's Built and Historic Environment) of the Core Strategy; and policies D4 (Designing in Context) and D11 (Alterations and Extension) of the Islington Unitary Development Plan (2002)."
